<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2159&amp;p=18095#p18095</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2159&amp;p=18095#p18095"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[MMC1 high bank switching mode]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2159&amp;p=18095#p18095"><![CDATA[
With the intermediate JMP approach, you can eliminate any decision logic from the IRQ handler itself, instead encoding that into the address to jump to. For example if you normally did X or Y in the handler, based on some zero-page variable, you'd just change the JMP address when this zero-page variable changed. This would be faster than the original code.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Fri Sep 29, 2006 12:10 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
